  m_Name: HeartSO
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::OrganSO
  Name: The Human Heart
  Description: 'The human heart is a vital muscular organ that acts as the core pump
    of the cardiovascular system. It continuously circulates blood, delivering essential
    oxygen and nutrients to the body''s tissues while removing waste products like
    carbon dioxide. To maintain this efficient one-way flow, the heart is divided
    into four distinct chambers: two upper atria that receive blood, and two lower
    ventricles that pump it back out.'
